Additionally, the use of matrix normal priors is a statistical technique commonly used in machine learning. 

The paper also involves object recognition, which suggests it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper's focus on transfer learning and feature transferability suggests it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The use of deep convolutional neural networks suggests it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language), which involves research on natural language processing and computer vision. 

Finally, the use of neural networks suggests it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which involves research on artificial neural networks and their applications.
